        <h2>Why Practice Gratitude?</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Improves Mental Health:</strong> Regularly acknowledging things we are thankful for can lower stress and anxiety levels.</li>
            <li><strong>Strengthens Relationships:</strong> Expressing gratitude can make others feel valued and deepen personal connections.</li>
            <li><strong>Enhances Overall Well-being:</strong> Gratitude increases positive emotions and helps create a positive outlook on life.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Practice Gratitude</h2>
        <p>There are many ways to incorporate gratitude into your daily life. Here are some ideas:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Keep a Gratitude Journal:</strong> Write down 3 things you are grateful for each day.</li>
            <li><strong>Say Thank You:</strong> Take time to express appreciation to others for their kindness.</li>
            <li><strong>Focus on the Present:</strong> Appreciate small moments and find joy in everyday experiences.</li>
            <li><strong>Reflect on Positive Memories:</strong> Think about past experiences that have brought you happiness.</li>
        </ul>

